different companies at once.

243
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:20,100
This makes it easy to
invest in a whole bunch

244
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:22,500
of companies all at the same time,

245
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:25,290
making your portfolio more diversified.

246
00:10:25,290 --> 00:10:26,910
Now, here's the best part.

247
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:30,090
What makes this even more
powerful is that it's going right

248
00:10:30,090 --> 00:10:33,480
inside my tax-advantaged account.

249
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:36,569
So not only do I get the
benefits of diversification

250
00:10:36,569 --> 00:10:38,040
and low cost,

251
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:41,190
but I also get to avoid
paying taxes on dividends

252
00:10:41,190 --> 00:10:43,380
or capital gains while it grows.

253
00:10:43,380 --> 00:10:46,650
This is perfect for my
$5-per-day challenge.

254
00:10:46,650 --> 00:10:48,570
Of course, it's important to remember

255
00:10:48,570 --> 00:10:50,970
that stocks can go up as well as down,

256
00:10:50,970 --> 00:10:54,390
and your capital is always
at risk when investing.

257
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:56,100
However, if you choose to invest

258
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:58,551
in an index fund like the S&P 500,

259
00:10:58,551 --> 00:11:00,330
which tracks the performance

260
00:11:00,330 --> 00:11:03,750
of the top publicly traded
companies in the United States,

261
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:06,120
it's worth noting that historically,

262
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,890
no one has lost money when they've bought

263
00:11:07,890 --> 00:11:09,510
and held for over 20 years.

264
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:12,720
Past performance isn't a
guarantee of future results,

265
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:16,200
but long-term investing in
diversified funds like this

266
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:19,710
can help reduce risk compared
to individual stocks.

267
00:11:19,710 --> 00:11:22,350
Let's head over to Trading 212,

268
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:23,400
and set this up.

269
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:24,233
To the left,

270
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:27,480
you can see this option to create a pie.

271
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,530
Once you click it,

272
00:11:28,530 --> 00:11:30,210
it gives you some different options

273
00:11:30,210 --> 00:11:32,190
like copy and model pies,

274
00:11:32,190 --> 00:11:34,860
looking at other people's
pies in the community

275
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:36,810
and creating your own custom pie.

276
00:11:36,810 --> 00:11:38,850
A pie is just a fancy way of showing you

277
00:11:38,850 --> 00:11:42,150
how your investments are divided
between different stocks.

278
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:44,430
For example, if you had $100

279
00:11:44,430 --> 00:11:47,970
and split it equally between
four individual stocks,

280
00:11:47,970 --> 00:11:52,500
your pie would have four
equal slices of 25% each.

281
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,720
We are gonna with the custom buy option

282
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,790
and click Add Instruments.

283
00:11:56,790 --> 00:12:01,790
I'm gonna search for a simple
Vanguard S&P 500 index fund.

284
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:04,770
As you can see, there are a
couple of different options.

285
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:07,050
One has Acc in brackets,

286
00:12:07,050 --> 00:12:09,360
and that stands for accumulation,

287
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:10,890
meaning that all your dividends

288
00:12:10,890 --> 00:12:13,830
are reinvested back into your investments.

289
00:12:13,830 --> 00:12:15,600
The other option looks the same

290
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:19,200
but has Dist in brackets at the end,

291
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,180
which is short for distribution.

292
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:22,530
This second option means

293
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:23,970
that you are given a dividends

294
00:12:23,970 --> 00:12:25,800
rather than them being automatically

295
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,600
reinvested into your account.

296
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:31,170
So for me, I want this challenge
to be as easy as possible,

297
00:12:31,170 --> 00:12:34,020
so I'll be choosing the accumulation one.

298
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:36,540
Now, I'm gonna click Add to pie.

299
00:12:36,540 --> 00:12:38,370
Alright, so we've got our account set up

300
00:12:38,370 --> 00:12:40,020
and decided what to invest in,

301
00:12:40,020 --> 00:12:42,300
but here comes the tedious part:

302
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:45,810
investing a fiver every single day.

303
00:12:45,810 --> 00:12:47,460
Honestly, I think a lot

304
00:12:47,460 --> 00:12:49,890
of the hate towards this
challenge comes from people

305
00:12:49,890 --> 00:12:53,610
imagining the effort it
takes to do this every day,

306
00:12:53,610 --> 00:12:56,880
but the truth is it really
doesn't have to be that hard.

307
00:12:56,880 --> 00:13:01,880
That's why step four is
to set up auto investing.

308
00:13:02,190 --> 00:13:05,100
Now, this feature isn't just
great for the $5 challenge.

309
00:13:05,100 --> 00:13:07,260
It's essential for any investor,

310
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:09,180
no matter how much you are putting in.

311
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:11,910
This is because it takes your
emotions out of investing

312
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:14,730
and leverages the power
of dollar cost averaging.

313
00:13:14,730 --> 00:13:15,780
Let me explain.

314
00:13:15,780 --> 00:13:17,280
The reality of the stock market

315
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:19,320
is that it's completely unpredictable.

316
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,420
It doesn't just move in one direction.

317
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:23,670
Sometimes the market will be going up.

318
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:26,010
Other days it'll be moving sideways,

319
00:13:26,010 --> 00:13:28,230
and then there are times
it'll be going down.

320
00:13:28,230 --> 00:13:29,610
When the market is down,

321
00:13:29,610 --> 00:13:31,590
your money actually buys more shares

322
00:13:31,590 --> 00:13:33,450
because prices are lower.

323
00:13:33,450 --> 00:13:36,330
For example, my $5 stretches further,

324
00:13:36,330 --> 00:13:39,540
letting me pick up more
shares at a discount.

325
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:43,290
And when the market is up,
my $5 buys fewer shares

326
00:13:43,290 --> 00:13:45,120
because prices are higher.

327
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:46,740
The idea is that over time,

328
00:13:46,740 --> 00:13:49,170
these ups and downs
balance each other out,

329
00:13:49,170 --> 00:13:51,960
which is the magic of
dollar cost averaging.

330
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:55,560
It's been such a reliable and
stress-free strategy for me

331
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:57,270
because it takes the pressure off trying

332
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:59,040
to time the market perfectly.

333
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,860
For this challenge, I'll be
using this exact strategy

334
00:14:01,860 --> 00:14:04,560
by investing the same
amount every single day,

335
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:06,090
and if you don't wanna do it daily,

336
00:14:06,090 --> 00:14:07,290
you can invest monthly

337
00:14:07,290 --> 00:14:08,940
and still see the same results.

338
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:10,260
It's entirely up to you.

339
00:14:10,260 --> 00:14:14,310
Let's go back to Trading
212 and click Next.

340
00:14:14,310 --> 00:14:16,350
This then gives us the
option to either choose

341
00:14:16,350 --> 00:14:20,070
to invest manually or use
the autoinvest feature.

342
00:14:20,070 --> 00:14:23,130
We're of course going
to select Autoinvest,

343
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:24,690
and then click Next.

344
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:27,630
Now, we have these three
sliders we can play around with.

345
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:30,240
The first one is our initial deposit.

346
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:32,730
This is the money we're gonna
be investing right away,

347
00:14:32,730 --> 00:14:36,060
so I'm gonna set this to five pounds.

348
00:14:36,060 --> 00:14:38,460
Next, we have the investment frequency.

349
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:40,800
As you can see, you can
do this every two months,

350
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,410
monthly, every two weeks, weekly,

351
00:14:43,410 --> 00:14:47,820
but we're gonna select the
daily option and press Update,

352
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:51,120
and then we're gonna change
this to five pound, too.

353
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:54,330
Finally, let's set the years to one.

354
00:14:54,330 --> 00:14:55,590
And as you can see,

355
00:14:55,590 --> 00:14:58,290
there's a cool value
projection graph at the top,

356
00:14:58,290 --> 00:15:00,210
which shows us what we can expect

357
00:15:00,210 --> 00:15:02,970
to make in a year based
on historical data.

358
00:15:02,970 --> 00:15:07,380
1,970 pounds may not seem super impressive

359
00:15:07,380 --> 00:15:09,960
when we're gonna be putting in 1.8K,

360
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:13,710
but if you move that slider
all the way to 40 years,

361
00:15:13,710 --> 00:15:16,380
look how compound interest takes over.

362
00:15:16,380 --> 00:15:18,210
This value projection says our

363
00:15:18,210 --> 00:15:19,950
little five-pound-a-day investment

364
00:15:19,950 --> 00:15:23,550
could be worth 5.52 million

365
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:27,180
from an investment of only 73,000 pounds.

366
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:29,580
Of course, this is all estimations,

367
00:15:29,580 --> 00:15:33,120
and if I were you, I'd take
this with a grain of salt,

368
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:35,790
as one knows what the market
is gonna do long term.

369
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:36,930
However, playing around

370
00:15:36,930 --> 00:15:39,270
with these compound
interest value projections

371
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,890
is very motivational.

372
00:15:40,890 --> 00:15:44,490
So let's bring it back to
one year and click Next.

373
00:15:44,490 --> 00:15:47,370
Now we get the chance
to name our investment.

374
00:15:47,370 --> 00:15:52,370
So I'm gonna call it Coffee a day,

375
00:15:52,770 --> 00:15:54,450
and then click Next.

376
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:56,040
Now it's time to fund the pie.

377
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,660
So let's click this,

378
00:15:57,660 --> 00:16:01,140
and as we've already funded
the Trading 212 account,

379
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:04,140
we can choose the Free funds option.

380
00:16:04,140 --> 00:16:05,700
This isn't free money.

381
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:08,970
It just takes cash from
your balance on Trading 212.

382
00:16:08,970 --> 00:16:12,090
So as long as we top this
account up every now and again,

383
00:16:12,090 --> 00:16:14,250
then the daily investment
should go through.

384
00:16:14,250 --> 00:16:16,860
Then, I just need to press Confirm,

385
00:16:16,860 --> 00:16:19,110
and boom, that's all set up.

386
00:16:19,110 --> 00:16:22,770
So a year from now, hope I'm still alive.

387
00:16:22,770 --> 00:16:24,233
I'll catch up with you.

388
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:26,816
(upbeat music)

389
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:30,733
Right, it is time to
check out the results.

390
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:33,270
I know I'm about five months late on this.

391
00:16:33,270 --> 00:16:35,850
That's how good the autoinvest feature is.

392
00:16:35,850 --> 00:16:38,580
You just forget it's
investing in the background.

393
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:41,100
But trust me, the results
are worth the weight.

394
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,600
They're really interesting.

395
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:46,410
I started this challenge
back in August, 2023,

396
00:16:46,410 --> 00:16:48,960
and after the first month I was up

397
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:51,600
two pounds and 37 pence,

398
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:54,510
which was a 1.5% return.

399
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:58,470
Not bad, but then September came along,

400
00:16:58,470 --> 00:17:00,660
and things didn't go quite so well.

401
00:17:00,660 --> 00:17:04,110
I was actually sitting
at a loss of 79 pence,

402
00:17:04,110 --> 00:17:07,860
which was a -0.5% return.

403
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:12,450
This right here is why so many
people give up on investing.

404
00:17:12,450 --> 00:17:13,950
In the first two months,

405
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:17,280
I had almost nothing to
show for my consistency.

406
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:18,600
It's no wonder people decide

407
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:19,770
to pull their money out

408
00:17:19,770 --> 00:17:21,540
when they don't see immediate results.

409
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:23,010
So I was determined to stick

410
00:17:23,010 --> 00:17:25,500
with my dollar cost averaging strategy,

411
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:26,850
and I'm so glad I did

412
00:17:26,850 --> 00:17:29,970
because things really
started to turn around.

413
00:17:29,970 --> 00:17:31,590
Fast forward six months,

414
00:17:31,590 --> 00:17:35,220
and I was up 83 pounds and 70 pence,

415
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:38,100
which is an 18.2% return.

416
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,150
Not too shabby.

417
00:17:39,150 --> 00:17:40,860
And then by 12 months,

418
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:45,540
I'd made 161 pounds and 34 pence in profit

419
00:17:45,540 --> 00:17:48,360
with an 18.1% return.

420
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:50,790
That's where the
autoinvesting feature stopped,

421
00:17:50,790 --> 00:17:53,640
but I've continued tracking
the growth since then.

422
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:55,230
Now, it's jump to today.

423
00:17:55,230 --> 00:17:57,900
This is where it gets a little bit crazy.

424
00:17:57,900 --> 00:18:02,900
In total, I've invested 1,505 pounds,

425
00:18:03,180 --> 00:18:06,950
but my investment is now
sitting at 1,972 pounds.

426
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:11,040
That means I've made a profit

427
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:14,730
of 467 pounds and three pence,

428
00:18:14,730 --> 00:18:16,650
which we can convert to dollars,

429
00:18:16,650 --> 00:18:18,970
and that works out at $576.59,

430
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:26,520
which is a staggering
43.8% rate of return.

431
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:27,870
Now, this is proof

432
00:18:27,870 --> 00:18:31,440
that time in the market
beats timing the market.

433
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:33,630
If I'd panicked and pulled my money out

434
00:18:33,630 --> 00:18:35,670
after losing some in a second month

435
00:18:35,670 --> 00:18:38,010
or stopped the challenge altogether,

436
00:18:38,010 --> 00:18:39,810
I'd never have reached this point.

437
00:18:39,810 --> 00:18:42,450
Even I couldn't have dreamt
of results like this.

438
00:18:42,450 --> 00:18:45,510
It's down to the wild year
the stock market has had.

439
00:18:45,510 --> 00:18:47,100
However, it's important to note

440
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:49,200
that these results are not typical,

441
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:52,680
and past performance doesn't
guarantee future results.

442
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:55,800
I'm thinking about continuing
this challenge long term

443
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:58,380
just to see how much it could grow.

444
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:00,120
If that's something you'd like to see,

445
00:19:00,120 --> 00:19:01,200
let me know in the comments,

446
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:03,720
and I'll make another
update video in the future.

447
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,973
If you wanna learn more
about how I pick my stocks,

448
00:19:05,973 --> 00:19:08,010
then I'm gonna leave that
video right up there,

449
00:19:08,010 --> 00:19:09,540
but don't click on it just yet.

450
00:19:09,540 --> 00:19:11,850
Make sure to subscribe if
you want to grow your wealth.

451
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:13,713
Okay, I'll see you over there.

